Architectural Roadmap Validated

Understood. Deferring the input sanitization to the background agent and the UI layer is a completely valid engineering decision. This approach keeps your API ingestion endpoints lightweight and fast, pushing the logical heavy lifting to the asynchronous discovery worker where it belongs.

Here is exactly how your system is already perfectly positioned to handle this future update:

    The AI Agent (Asynchronous Discovery): Later, when you expand your background discovery.ts agent, it will pick up these /auth/login URLs that are currently sitting in the PENDING_DISCOVERY state. When the agent attempts to parse the HTML, it will detect the authentication wall. Instead of crashing, the agent will simply update that specific category's validationStatus in the database to a restrictive state (e.g., FAILED or a custom AUTH_WALL status).

    The UI Layer (User Feedback): Because you have already built a highly modular UI in source-manager.vue, the moment the database status changes, the reactive state will automatically pull that URL out of the "Active" zone and drop it into your pre-existing Restricted Sources zone. You will merely need to add one new switch case to your getBadges() utility function to render a red "Auth Required" or "No News Reachable" tag.
